<subsection xml:id="subsec-plotting-points-and-shapes-on-a-coordinate-plane">
    <title>Plotting Points and Shapes on a Cartesian Plane</title>
    <p>
        Coordinates represents a pair of numbers written as <m>(x, y)</m> that represents a pointâ€™s location on the Cartesian plane, 
        where "x" tells you how far to move left or right, and "y" tells you how far to move up or down on the Cartesian plane.
    </p>
    <p>
        If your point is (3,4), move 3 units right (positive x direction) and 4 units up (positive y direction).
    </p>
    <p>
        If the point is (-2, -5), move 2 units left (negative x direction) and 5 units down (negative y direction).
    </p>
    <p>
        Once you've moved to the correct location, mark it on the plane!
    </p>
    <activity>
        <statement>
        <p>
            <term>Work in groups</term>
        </p>
        <p>
            Consider the points: <m>A(2,3)</m>, <m>B(2,7)</m>, <m>C(6,7)</m>, <m>D(6,3)</m>
            <ol marker="(a).">
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Draw a Cartesian plane and plot the given points.
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Identify the shape formed by connecting the points.
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Discuss as a group and compare your graphs with the rest in class.
                    </p>
                </li>
            </ol>
        </p>
    </statement>
    <solution>
        <p>
           The plotted points are as shown 
        </p>
        <image>
            <latex-image label="coordinate_points">
                \begin{tikzpicture}
                % Draw grid
                \draw[very thin,gray!50] (0,0) grid (8,8);
                
                % Draw x and y axes
                \draw[thick,-&gt;] (-1,0) -- (8.5,0) node[anchor=north] {\textbf{x}};
                \draw[thick,-&gt;] (0,-1) -- (0,8.5) node[anchor=east] {\textbf{y}};
                
                % Tick marks and labels
                \foreach \x in {1,2,3,4,5,6,7,8} {
                    \draw[thick] (\x,-0.1) -- (\x,0.1);
                    \node[anchor=north] at (\x,-0.2) {\textbf{\x}};
                }

                \foreach \y in {1,2,3,4,5,6,7,8} {
                    \draw[thick] (-0.1,\y) -- (0.1,\y);
                    \node[anchor=east] at (-0.2,\y) {\textbf{\y}};
                }

                % Origin
                \node[anchor=north east] at (-0.1,-0.1) {\textbf{0}};

                % Plot points and labels
                \fill[red] (2,3) circle (3pt) node[anchor=north east] {\textbf{A}};
                \fill[blue] (2,7) circle (3pt) node[anchor=south east] {\textbf{B}};
                \fill[green] (6,7) circle (3pt) node[anchor=south west] {\textbf{C}};
                \fill[orange] (6,3) circle (3pt) node[anchor=north west] {\textbf{D}};

                % Connect the points to form a rectangle
                \draw[thick] (2,3) -- (2,7) -- (6,7) -- (6,3) -- cycle;
                \end{tikzpicture}
            </latex-image>
        </image>
    </solution>
        
    </activity>
    
